 and management of live video and associated data. The Company operates in two divisions: Pebble Beach Systems and Vislink Communication Systems. Pebble Beach Systems division is focused on broadcast software and is responsible for the sales and marketing of its software products and services. The Vislink Communication Systems division is a consolidation of its hardware technology businesses and is responsible for the sales and marketing of its hardware products and services. It is also the product center for the Advent satcom communication products, Link and Gigawave wireless camera systems and microwave and amplifier products. It provides solutions to three markets: broadcast communications market, for live news, sport and entertainment events; surveillance, public safety and defense markets, to enable real-time video intelligence, and the broadcast software market, for the acquisition, management and playout of media and content.','Naked Trader','gbp','United Kingdom','LSE','technology',NULL,'2014-03-05 14:03:27','2016-09-21 12:09:15','','','http://www.vislink.com','','','27 Maylands Avenue\r\nHEMEL HEMPSTEAD, HP2 7DE\r\nUnited Kingdom - Map\r\n+44-1442-431300 (Phone)\r\n+44-1442-431333 (Fax)',NULL,15.3800,'11:17 21-Sep-2016','2016-09-21 12:09:15',0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,NULL,0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,NULL),(14,'Debenhams','DEB','Debenhams is a department store group that floated on the market in 2006, three years after being taken private by private equity groups CVC, Merrill Lynch and Texas Pacific. The group has over 120 stores across the UK and Ireland with around 20,000 employees. Debenhams also has a further 29 international franchise stores in 14 countries.\r\n\r\nDebenhams plc is a United Kingdom-based multi-channel company. The Company brand trades through approximately 240 stores in 28 countries. It is available online in more than 70 countries. It owns and operates 172 stores in the United Kingdom, Republic of Ireland and Denmark. Its product portfolio includes women’s wear, menswear, children’s wear, and health and beauty products. It also offer customers a range of services, including restaurants and cafes, personal shopping assistance, hairdressing and beauty treatments, nail bars and wedding/celebration gift services. Its Website stocks a range of own label, Designers at Debenhams and international brands, and a range of concessions. It also offers furniture, electrical appliances and flowers002E','Motley Fool Pro','gbp','United Kingdom','LSE','cyclical',NULL,'2014-03-05 14:04:20','2016-10-17 14:58:51','','','http://phx.corporate-ir.net/frame.zhtml?c=196805&p=index','','','Regent\'s Place, 10 Brock Street\r\nLONDON, NW1 3FG\r\nUnited Kingdom - Map\r\n+44-20-74084444 (Phone)',NULL,54.0040,'15:43 17-Oct-2016','2016-10-17 14:58:51',0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,NULL,0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,0.0000,NULL),(15,'ARM Holdings','ARM','ARM designs microchips for use in mobile phones, computers.\r\n\r\nARM Holdings plc (ARM) is a United Kingdom-based company engaged in designing of microprocessors, physical intellectual property (IP) and related technology and software, and sale of development tools. The Company\'s offers products, such as 16/32/64-bit RISC microprocessors, data engines, graphics processors, digital libraries, embedded memories, peripherals, software and development tools, as well as analog functions and high-speed connectivity products. The Company\'s product offering includes microprocessor Cores, physical IP, development tools and support and maintenance services. ARM licenses and sells its technology and products to international electronics companies, which in turn manufacture, market and sell microprocessors, application-specific integrated circuits (ASICs), application-specific standard processors (ASSPs) and microcontrollers (MCUs) based on ARM\'s technology to systems companies for incorporation into a variety of end products.','Own bat?  Motley Fool book from the 90s','gbp','United Kingdom','L